Format the output as a plain text script for Fish Audio.
Do NOT use speaker labels (e.g. "Ava:", "Narrator:") anywhere.

You MUST use Fish Audio "Emotion Control" tags to guide the prosody.
Embed the tags naturally before sentences or clauses where the emotion applies.

Supported Tags:
[Basic Emotions]:
[calm] [happy] [sad] [angry] [fearful] [disgusted] [surprised]

[Advanced Emotions]:
[excited] [serious] [friendly] [comforting] [suspenseful] [mysterious] [urgent] [relaxed]
[nostalgic] [melancholic] [hopeful] [romantic] [dreamy] [confused] [proud] [guilty]
[ashamed] [envious] [sympathetic] [apathetic] [bored] [painful] [sick] [tired]

[Tone Markers]:
[whisper] [shout] [scream] [cry] [laugh] [moan] [groan] [gasp] [sigh] [pant]
[chuckle] [giggle] [sob] [whimper] [sniffle] [snort] [scoff] [sneer] [growl]

[Effect Tags]:
[speed_up] [speed_down] [pitch_up] [pitch_down] [volume_up] [volume_down]

Example:
"[excited] Look at that magnificent view! [calm] It reminds me of the history of this place."
